<p>Explain the code <strong>you wrote in today's lesson</strong>. Record a short video on your phone — you may show your player turning left and right while it runs. Try to use these words: <strong>facing</strong>, <strong>draw_player</strong>, <strong>offset</strong>, <strong>direction</strong>, <strong>function</strong>.</p>
<blockquote>
<ol>
<li>Show your player facing right, then left.</li>
<li>Point at your <code>facing</code> variable and say when it changes.</li>
<li>Read your eye-position line out loud and explain the offset.</li>
<li>Show one choice you made in your code and why.</li>
</ol>
